---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
import { SITE_CONFIG } from '~/lib/siteConfig'

const updated = '2026-06-20'
---

<BaseLayout
  title={`About — oriz · cards`}
  description={`About cards.oriz.in: ${SITE_CONFIG.tagline}`}
>
  <div class="spine-prose">
    <header class="page-head">
      <p class="eyebrow mono"><a href="/">cards</a> / about</p>
      <h1>about</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        A Bloomberg-terminal-for-Indian-credit-cards. Every fee, every reward
        rate, every late charge, in one ledger. No rosettes, no editor's
        picks, no affiliate steering.
      </p>
      <p class="meta">Last updated: {updated}</p>
    </header>

    <article class="prose">
      <h2 id="what-this-is">What this is</h2>
      <p>
        cards.oriz.in is a static catalogue of <strong>750 cards</strong> issued
        in India — credit, debit, and prepaid — across 35 issuers including
        Amex, Axis, AU SFB, Bandhan, BoB, BoM, Canara, CUB, DCB, Dhanlaxmi,
        ESAF, Federal, HDFC, HSBC, ICICI, IDBI, IDFC, Indian Bank, IndusInd,
        IOB, J&K Bank, Karnataka Bank, Kotak, KVB, PNB, PSB, RBL, Saraswat,
        SBI, SIB, StanChart, TMB, UCO, Union, and Yes Bank.
      </p>
      <p>
        Banks publish card terms across PDFs, microsites, and FAQ pages that
        change without notice. cards.oriz.in pulls those into a single,
        searchable, comparable form — open data, open source, no affiliate
        gating.
      </p>

      <h2 id="methodology">Methodology</h2>
      <p>
        Each card profile is assembled from the <strong>Most Important Terms
        and Conditions</strong> (MITC) and <strong>Key Fact Statement</strong>
        (KFS) PDFs the issuer publishes — both of which are mandated by RBI
        and updated when fees change. We extract the standard fields (joining
        fee, annual fee, APR, fuel waiver, lounge access, eligibility,
        insurance) into a normalised schema. Every value is a number — no
        marketing copy in the data tier.
      </p>
      <p>
        We don't take affiliate commissions and we don't accept paid placement.
        The choice of which cards to list is the entire universe of cards
        published by the 35 issuers — there is no editor.
      </p>

      <h2 id="sources">Sources</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>RBI Master Direction on Credit Card and Debit Card</strong> — the regulatory baseline.</li>
        <li><strong>Issuer MITC documents</strong> — fees, charges, late-payment, over-limit, currency markup.</li>
        <li><strong>Issuer KFS documents</strong> — APR, billing cycle, grace period, minimum-due rules.</li>
        <li><strong>Issuer card pages</strong> — rewards tables, lounge programmes, fuel waiver windows, eligibility.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Our extraction date is stamped on each card profile. The footer below
        shows the most-recent rebuild timestamp for the whole catalogue.
      </p>

      <h2 id="licence">Licence</h2>
      <p>
        Card data on cards.oriz.in is published under
        <strong>Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International</strong> (CC BY
        4.0). Take a copy, redistribute, build on it — please credit
        cards.oriz.in and link back. The data is also available as a single
        JSON dump: <a href="/cards.json">/cards.json</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Part of oriz</h2>
      <p>
        cards is one site in the <a href="https://oriz.in/">oriz</a> family —
        small, free, open-source tools by Chirag Singhal. One sign-in works
        across every site. Visit the
        <a href="https://oriz.in/">hub</a> for the rest.
      </p>

      <h2>Source</h2>
      <p>
        Code: <a href="https://github.com/chirag127/oriz-cards">github.com/chirag127/oriz-cards</a>.
        Issues, corrections, and PRs welcome.
      </p>

      <h2>Disclaimer</h2>
      <p>
        Information here is for reference. It is not financial advice and may
        lag the bank's own page by days or weeks. Always verify on the
        issuing bank's site before applying. See the
        <a href="/legal/disclaimer/">full disclaimer</a>.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
